Program: Outlook
Title: 18/09/2009
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0047wwr
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 18 Sep 2009
KHALED HOSSEINI Best selling author Khaled Hosseini, returns to his war torn home in Kabul and recalls the very different country he lived in as a child. EGYPT ILLEGAL ADOPTION Two American couples have been convicted in Egypt of trying to adopt children illegally. The case highlights the complicated laws surrounding the care of orphans in the country. FACING UP TO INTERNET ADDICTION 19 year old Ben Alexander from Colorado explains how he became addicted to online games and the special treatment he needed to free him from his computer. Show less